ife?'She shrugged. 'What about it?''Aren't you worried about, like, forever?''Forever is composed of nows,' she says.\n\n- John Green, Paper Towns\n|\nSometimes the heart speaks, and the brain does not understand the language.\n\n- T.A. Cline, Archomai\n|\nBe aware of the high notes, of the blissful faces and their soft messages, and listen for the silent message of a highly decorated gift.\n\n- Dejan\n|\nLove simply, perpetually exists and that it’s a matter of psychic housekeeping to make room for it.\n\n- Sharon Salzberg, Real Love: The Art of Mindful Connection"